item.title: What do i do if it sais my account is already logged in or is disabled/locked?
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

[quote=“I Br3ndan I, post:2, topic:85386”]If it says you’re account has been disabled when you try to login, it means you’re account has been banned. Try using another name, if that doesn’t work it means you’ve been IP banned.

If it says you’re account is already logged in when you try to login, it means the server has crashed.

What does IP banned mean? When you’re IP banned you will not be able to connect to that specific server with any account name in the future because the owner has banned you’re IP address.

What does crash mean? When a server crashes, it goes offline and creates lagg for the owner of the server. This is mostly caused by nulls. [/quote]

Yeah just about what he said.

An I.P. ban doesn’t let the server accept packets from your computer which doesn’t let you log in. When the server crashes it means that the servers bandwidth has hit maximum level with information and can’t hold so much of it.
